WEBVTT

00:04.080 --> 00:06.340
Hey, this is a good box.

00:06.450 --> 00:08.600
We got a bloody foot on a hook...

00:09.680 --> 00:11.740
... and a dissected alien...

00:12.590 --> 00:14.750
... and some tax returns.

00:14.850 --> 00:16.290
Oooooh!

00:16.390 --> 00:19.219
The IRS believes we have a home office.

00:19.220 --> 00:21.799
- Oooooh!
- Oooooh!

00:21.800 --> 00:23.890
Oh, my God! You guys are
not gonna believe it!

00:24.000 --> 00:25.860
I passed my driving test!

00:25.970 --> 00:28.660
Apparently, it's "pass everyone" day.

00:29.000 --> 00:30.980
Come on. I'm not that bad a driver.

00:31.000 --> 00:32.030
I let you drive home,

00:32.040 --> 00:34.570
and you made a garbage truck swerve.

00:34.670 --> 00:35.950
You don't see something that big

00:35.980 --> 00:38.380
up on two wheels every day.

00:38.840 --> 00:41.100
It's like he was
stopping at every house.

00:41.140 --> 00:43.010
That's what they do!

00:45.280 --> 00:46.520
And then, to finish up,

00:46.550 --> 00:48.950
you dragged a traffic cone
most of the way home.

00:48.960 --> 00:51.440
Luckily, that kid's
skateboard broke it loose.

00:51.460 --> 00:52.590
I need a drink.

00:52.600 --> 00:54.490
Becky, where do you keep the hard stuff?

00:54.590 --> 00:55.790
In Becky.

00:57.460 --> 00:59.860
So, can I use Grandma's old car now?

00:59.970 --> 01:00.970
Yeah.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.180
But not to drive.

01:02.640 --> 01:04.670
You can sit in it and play the radio

01:04.769 --> 01:06.370
and go, "Vroom, vroom!"

01:06.470 --> 01:09.510
Your imagination is a road to anywhere.

01:14.150 --> 01:16.780
Well, I really do need the job.

01:16.880 --> 01:18.750
And, boy, do I love housecleaning.

01:20.320 --> 01:21.720
It's topless?

01:21.820 --> 01:24.720
Well, that explains the $40 an hour.

01:24.820 --> 01:27.260
$40 an hour? Do they take men?

01:27.360 --> 01:29.380
'Cause I'll show off the girls for that.

01:30.300 --> 01:32.499
Um, I'm gonna have to pass.

01:32.500 --> 01:34.320
But I will give your
number to my sister.

01:34.420 --> 01:35.870
Thank you.

01:35.970 --> 01:38.890
All right, so, since I've
got you guys here together,

01:38.900 --> 01:40.940
I want to show you my costume.

01:42.260 --> 01:44.840
Disemboweled cheerleader.

01:44.940 --> 01:48.890
Ohhh! Look at you, all gory and sexy.

01:48.900 --> 01:50.800
Uh, I'm bringing a friend to the party,

01:50.860 --> 01:52.880
and it looks like it's
starting to be a thing,

01:52.990 --> 01:54.950
so I wanted to show off a little leg,

01:55.050 --> 01:56.220
a little intestine.

01:57.520 --> 01:58.680
Who's the lucky guy?

01:58.720 --> 02:00.060
His name's Peter.

02:00.160 --> 02:03.219
Oh! Peter!

02:03.220 --> 02:06.000
I want your opinion. I do
not want you teasing him.

02:06.180 --> 02:08.039
This family has a history of chasing off

02:08.060 --> 02:10.199
all the unstable men that
I bring into my life,

02:10.300 --> 02:12.740
but Peter's different.

02:12.820 --> 02:14.970
Oh! Peter!

02:15.070 --> 02:17.640
He's different!

02:17.740 --> 02:20.340
I'm serious... no teasing.

02:20.480 --> 02:22.026
Don't worry. We'll be good.

02:22.050 --> 02:24.720
Yeah, you haven't dated
anyone in, like, forever.

02:24.820 --> 02:27.470
We're not gonna mess with
whatever straggling animal

02:27.490 --> 02:29.350
you've picked off the back of the herd.

